🎮 **Custom exceptions provide domain-specific error handling.**

**Creating a custom exception:**
```cpp
class GameException : public std::exception {
private:
    std::string message;

public:
    GameException(const std::string& msg) : message(msg) {}

    const char* what() const noexcept override {
        return message.c_str();
    }
};
```

**Derived custom exceptions:**
```cpp
class PlayerNotFoundException : public GameException {
public:
    PlayerNotFoundException(const std::string& name) 
        : GameException("Player '" + name + "' not found!") {}
};
```

**Benefits of custom exceptions:**

| Benefit | Why |
|---------|-----|
| **Clear messages** | Domain-specific errors |
| **Type safety** | Catch specific errors |
| **Extra data** | Store error details |
| **Maintainability** | Clear error handling |

**Game uses:**

| Use | Example |
|-----|---------|
| **Player errors** | Player not found |
| **Inventory errors** | Item not found |
| **Combat errors** | Invalid target |
| **Save errors** | Save file corrupted |

